.TH NSDELCOMMENT 1 "$Date: 2008/05/05 13:08:53 $" CASTOR "Cns User Commands"
.SH NAME
nsdelcomment \- delete the comment associated with a file/directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nsdelcomment
.I path
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nsdelcomment
deletes the comment associated with a file/directory in the CASTOR
name server.
.LP
The effective user ID of the process must match the owner of the file or
the caller must have GRP_ADMIN or ADMIN privileges in the Cupv database.
.TP
.I path
specifies the CASTOR pathname.
If
.I path
does not start with
.BR / ,
it is prefixed by the content of the
.B CASTOR_HOME
environment variable.
.SH EXIT STATUS
This program returns 0 if the operation was successful or >0 if the operation
failed.
